text: Woodies may refer to: * The Woodies, nickname given to men's tennis doubles team whose members were Todd Woodbridge and Mark Woodforde * Woodie's DIY, a DIY store chain operated by the Grafton Group * MTV Woodies, a music awards show by college channel mtvU * Woodward & Lothrop, a defunct department store * Woodies, another name for Cuisenaire rods * Woodies, a nickname for Woodbine cigarettes * Woodroofe, a South Australian soft drink brandname and historic company == See also == * Woodie (disambiguation) * Woody (disambiguation)
title: Woodies
